futurelivinglab.caption:
This summer, members competed in the Banaue Lodge Competition held by Terraviva. They were tasked to reimagine a sustainable lodging structure that promotes local traditions and tourism of Banaue Rice Terraces while harnessing the essence of this UNESCO site. 

Team members: Ambareen Fatima, Chidubem Nwokeocha, Emma Saville and Sara Oureshi.

‚ÄúDue to the decline in the Banaue‚Äôs population and the commodification of their culture, Ifugo traditions have become disturbed with the ideals of tourism. Payoh Bale Lodge aims to reverse this trend by incorporating traditional Ifugao elements into its design as a method of cultural preservation and education for tourists. Inspired by the architecture in Batad Philippines, this proposal serves as a lodge in the Banaue area. Using local and traditional materials, the design respects and appreciates the Ifugao Houses, a traditional structure in the Philippines.‚Äù
